{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nPass 3 of the GitHub Code Quality remediation. Of 230 'present' findings, 201 (import-style + config_schema table lambdas) are dismissed as churn/intentional. This ticket remediates the subset that genuinely improves reliability/maintainability, in a single change. Two items originally scoped were reclassified as FALSE POSITIVES during verification and carry NO code change (see below).\n\n## Scope\n### Tier 1 (real gains)\n- reconcile_helpers.py (AI-1): when no_sync=False, _env=None inherits the parent env, so a caller's REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off silently suppresses the live sync pull. Build an explicit env dict; set REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off only when no_sync=True; strip the key on the live path. Add a regression test asserting the live path is unaffected by an ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off.\n- tests/unit/grounding (_HAVE_ASTGREP #310/#311): capability flag defined but never used in a skipif while siblings are — wire the guard where an ast-grep-dependent test needs it, or remove the dead flag if none does.\n- test_validation_depth.py (AI-3b): add non-review category coverage (e.g. category: transform) proving validation is category-agnostic.\n### Tier 2 (safe cleanup — VERIFIED unreferenced before removal)\n- Remove 15 genuinely-dead symbols: acli_graph dead _RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK dup; reconcile_check reverse maps (_TYPE_JIRA_TO_LOCAL, _PRIORITY_JIRA_TO_LOCAL); _engine_support/reads dead _SCRIPTS_DIR + its orphaned import; grounding/resolve _REFUTE_ELIGIBLE_KINDS; dead test-fixture constants (_UUID_*/_ALIAS_*/_ENGINE_DIR) in graph/_helpers, test_reducer_links, test_reducer_tag_delta, test_ticket_unblock, test_read_latest_status_reducer; dead nested def _boom in test_overlap_judge.\n- runners.py (#450): align base/override run() signature.\n### Reclassified as FALSE POSITIVE (NO code change; add to dismiss ledger)\n- #291 _SCAN_MAX_FILES: NOT dead — imported and enforced in pai_tools.search_files (lines 126-129), identity-pinned by two tests. CodeQL 'unused in-module' FP (enforcement is cross-module).\n- #766 _KINDS: referenced by test_deprecation_registry.py:40. FP.\n- #773/#774, #769-771, #794: skipped — real module caches (global), cross-module-wired candidate tuples (oracle.py), and a harmless test fixture, respectively.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] AI-1 fixed with a regression test that asserts the live (no_sync=False) subprocess env has REBAR_SYNC_PULL stripped even when the parent env sets it off, and no_sync=True still sets it off.\n- [ ] _HAVE_ASTGREP either guards an ast-grep test or is removed; no unused capability flag remains.\n- [ ] AI-3b: a non-review category test case added and passing.\n- [ ] The 15 Tier-2 symbols removed, each verified unreferenced repo-wide; behavior-preserving.\n- [ ] runners.py base/override signatures aligned.\n- [ ] _SCAN_MAX_FILES and _KINDS left intact (verified live; recorded as false positives).\n- [ ] make lint + mypy clean; touched test modules pass; single Gerrit change lands only after LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784432674014794001,"uuid":"edc93179-2ba7-4c74-8505-088ce6c2928b"}